('shipstad', 1967, 'Shipstad Hall was built in 1967 on the site of what was once a five-hole golf course. The hall is named for the Eddie Shipstad family, one-time owners of the Ice Follies, who were the building''s primary benefactors.', 'initialApp\\public\\archiveContent\\shipstad\\1967.JPG'),
('shipstad', 1987, 'Shipstad housed men for its first 20 years and then in the fall of 1987, it became the University''s first coed hall.', 'initialApp\\public\\archiveContent\\shipstad\\1987.JPG'),
('shipstad', 2008, 'The hall is also home to the University Archives and the University''s Heritage Museum, both located in the building''s basement.', 'initialApp\\public\\archiveContent\\shipstad\\2008.jpg'),
('shipstad', 2013, 'Shipstad Hall is closed its doors for the 2023-2024 school year in order to make a variety of renovations, and is officially reopening for the 2025-2026 school year.', 'initialApp\\public\\archiveContent\\shipstad\\2013.JPG'),

('merlo', 1990, 'Construction on the Harry A. Merlo Field began on April 23, 1990. A portion of the stadium construction project included the redesigning of the Chiles Center entrance and modifying the main parking lot.', 'initialApp\\public\\archiveContent\\merlo\\1990.jpg'),
('merlo', 1991, 'The field was dedicated on September 23, 1990 along with the first game being played against the University of Washington. The first game with the fully completed stadium including the permanent grand-stand was August 31, 1991.', 'initialApp\\public\\archiveContent\\merlo\\1991.JPG'),
('merlo', 2002, 'The women''s soccer team won the University of Portland''s first ever national championship in any sport in 2002, making the new soccer field worth the investment after they captured the title.', 'initialApp\\public\\archiveContent\\merlo\\2002.jpg')